IDOR 

Insecure Direct Object Reference: are a type access control vulnerability that arises when an application uses user-supplied input to access object directly. 

Happens: this type of vulnerability can occur when a web-server receives user-supplied input to retrieve objects (files, documents, data),
to much trust has been placed on the input data, and it is not validated on the server-side to confirm the requested object belongs to the user requesting it. 

Where are IDORs Located 
The Vulnerable endpoint your targeting may not always be something you see in the address bar. 
It could be content your browser loads in Via an "AJAX request" or something that find referenced in a JavaScript file. 

sometimes endpoints could have an unreferenced parameter that may have been of some use during development and got pushed to production. 
